**A research-grade stochastic dynamic transit routing platform for public transportation networks under travel-time uncertainty.**

Stochastic Transit Router (STR) integrates official schedule data (GTFS), real-time feeds (GTFS-Realtime), historical observations (NYC TLC), and pedestrian networks (OpenStreetMap) to compute both **deterministic fastest routes** and **risk-aware alternatives** with provenance tracking and reproducible results. Designed for algorithm researchers, transportation engineers, and operations teams needing intelligent routing under uncertainty.

**Current Version:** 0.1.0 (Foundational Release)
**License:** European Union Public Licence v1.2 (EUPL-1.2)
**Language:** Python 3.12+
**Platform Support:** Linux, macOS, Windows
**Maintained by:** [Zakir Bayramov](mailto:zakirbayramov942@gmail.com), [Gustav Olaf Yunus Laitinen-Lundström Fredriksson-Imanov](mailto:olaf.laitinen@uni.lu)

