## Quick Start

### Prerequisites
```
Python 3.12+
pip, setuptools, wheel
Git
2+ GB disk space (NYC data)
~5 minutes setup time
```

### Installation

```bash
# 1. Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/Zakir060/stochastic-transit-router.git
cd stochastic-transit-router

# 2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # Windows: .venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

# 3. Upgrade pip and install
python -m pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel
python -m pip install -e ".[dev,test,benchmarks,notebooks]"

# 4. Setup pre-commit hooks
pre-commit install

# 5. Verify installation
pytest -q
```

**Expected output:** smoke tests pass
**Time:** ~3-5 minutes (depending on internet speed)

### First Route Query

#### Via API
```bash
# Terminal 1: Start API server
uvicorn src.api.app:app --reload --port 8000

# Terminal 2: Query routes
curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/routes" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"source":"A","destination":"D","departure_time":"2026-04-05T08:00:00Z","objective":"fastest"}'
```

#### Via CLI
```bash
# Direct command-line query
python -m src.cli.main route A D
```

**Response includes:**
- Optimal route with legs (transit, walking)
- Estimated duration and arrival time
- Confidence (for stochastic routing)
- Alternative routes (top-3)

---

## Architecture

### High-Level Overview

```
User Request (API/CLI)
    ↓
Configuration Manager [Load route params, algorithm, preferences]
    ↓
Graph Loader [NYC transit graph ~500MB, pre-serialized]
    ↓
Routing Service [Algorithm selection layer]
    ├── Dijkstra [Deterministic shortest path]
    ├── A* [Heuristic-guided search]
    └── Yen's [K-shortest paths]
    ↓
Result Formatter [JSON/table output]
    ↓
Response (REST/CLI output)
```

### Module Organization

```
src/
├── api/                  # FastAPI REST endpoints
│   ├── app.py           # Application factory
│   ├── routers/         # Endpoint handlers
│   └── deps.py          # Dependency injection
├── cli/                 # Click command-line interface
├── service/             # Shared routing logic (used by API+CLI)
├── graph/               # Graph data structure & algorithms
│   ├── builder.py       # Graph construction from GTFS/OSM
│   ├── algorithms.py    # Dijkstra, A*, Yen's implementation
│   └── serialization.py # Pickle handling
├── gtfs/                # GTFS parsing & validation
├── gtfs_realtime/       # Real-time feed handling
├── osm/                 # OpenStreetMap integration
├── tlc/                 # NYC taxi data analysis
├── ingest/              # Data pipeline orchestration
├── stats/               # Statistical inference
├── risk/                # Risk metric computation
├── models/              # Pydantic data models
├── config/              # Configuration management
└── evaluation/          # Experiment runner

tests/
├── unit/                # Unit tests (isolated components)
├── integration/         # Integration tests (API+graph)
└── benchmark/           # Performance tests
```

### Data Flow

**Offline (One-time):**
```
Official Sources (GTFS ZIP, OSM JSON, TLC Parquet)
    → Download & Validate (scripts/download_official_data.py)
    → Parse (src/gtfs/loader.py, src/osm/parser.py)
    → Build Graph (src/graph/builder.py)
    → Serialize (pickle → data/processed/graph/nyc_*.pkl)
    → Record Provenance (data/manifests/runs/*.json)
```

**Online (Per-request):**
```
Request (origin, destination, time)
    → Load Graph (~2 seconds)
    → Route Algorithms (20-100ms)
    → Format Response
    → Serve JSON/Table
```

