## Data Sources

### Official Public Data

| Source | Coverage | Format | Volume | Freshness | License |
|--------|----------|--------|--------|-----------|---------|
| **GTFS** | NYC MTA transit network | ZIP archive | ~100MB | Weekly | WTFPL |
| **GTFS-Realtime** | Live delays/alerts | Protocol Buffer | Live stream | 30-60 sec | WTFPL |
| **OpenStreetMap** | Pedestrian network | JSON/XML | ~50MB NYC | Community | ODbL |
| **NYC TLC** | Taxi/FHV trips | Parquet | ~50GB/month | 30-day lag | CC0 |

### Data Quality Standards

All data passes:
- ✓ SHA-256 integrity verification
- ✓ GTFS schema validation
- ✓ Referential integrity checks
- ✓ Logical constraint validation (arrival < departure)
- ✓ Geospatial bounds checking

**Reproducibility:** Every run records:
- Source URL and acquisition timestamp
- SHA-256 hash of downloaded file
- Python version and system info
- Processing duration
- Graph statistics (nodes, edges, components)

