## Debugging & Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

| Issue | Cause | Solution |
|-------|-------|----------|
| **Slow routes** | Large graph, no heuristic | Use A* instead of Dijkstra |
| **API timeout** | Complex query | Reduce K in Yen's algorithm |
| **Memory spike** | Full graph loading | Pre-warmup graph in startup |
| **Stale data** | Old feed cache | Clear data/cache/ directory |

### Debug Mode

```bash
# Verbose logging
LOGLEVEL=DEBUG python -m src.cli.main routes --origin 123 --destination 456

# Profile performance
python -m cProfile -s cumtime src.cli.main routes --origin 123 --destination 456

# Trace algorithm execution
python -c "
from src.graph import load_graph
from src.algorithms import dijkstra

graph = load_graph('data/processed/graph/nyc.pkl')
route = dijkstra(graph, 123, 456, 1712282400, debug=True)
print(route)
"
```

### Health Checks

```bash
# API health
curl http://localhost:8000/api/health

# Graph integrity
python -c "from src.graph import validate_graph; validate_graph('data/processed/graph/nyc.pkl')"

# Feed freshness
python -m src.cli.main feeds status
```

